15/03/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Former Prime Minister Adrian Nastase announced on Wednesday (15 March) that he has resigned as speaker of parliament's Chamber of Deputies, as well as from his post in the main opposition Social Democratic Party. On Tuesday, the party approved a no-confidence motion against him. Nastase is being investigated for corruption, stemming from real estate deals. He insists the allegations are politically motivated. (Rompres, Nine o'clock - 15/03/06)
